An intercity train runs between Guangzhou and Shenzhen in South China's Guangdong Province. Photo: China Railway Sina WeiboMobile payments with facial-recognition technology can now be used to board the intercity train between Guangzhou and Shenzhen in South China's Guangdong Province. The technology will reduce the time it takes to carry out identification checks and ensure that passengers themselves have bought their tickets, instead of ticket scalpers, media reported on Sunday.It takes three seconds to scan a code on your WeChat app. Then you can pass the ticket gate and take the Guangzhou-Shenzhen intercity train, saving at least 15 minutes. Payment is made via WeChat Pay.Before taking the train, passengers can register in the WeChat mini-program "Guangdong-Shenzhen intercity pass" for identification authentication and facial recognition, chinanews.com reported on Sunday, citing the head of the passenger department of China Railway Guangzhou Group. After successfully registering, passengers can use a code on WeChat to enter and exit the station. Payment will be taken upon departure from the station.According to the company, the Guangzhou-Shenzhen intercity railway runs 85 pairs of trains, carrying 106,000 passengers every day.  
